1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nc3 Qc7 6. g3 Nf6 7. Ndb5 { When a smaller value piece attacks a larger value piece, it generates time. } 7... Qb8 8. Bf4 Ne5 9. Bxe5 { Captures gain time. } 9... Qxe5 10. f4 Qb8 11. Be2 { [%csl Ge2] } 11... Bc5 12. e5 a6 13. exf6 axb5 { [%csl Gb5][%cal Gf6g7] } 14. fxg7 Rg8 15. Ne4 { The 3rd way to gain time or manipulate time at all in chess is to make a threat. } 15... Be7 16. Qd4 Ra4 17. Nf6+ Kd8 (17... Bxf6 18. Qxf6 Qd6) 18. Qxa4 (18. Qb6+ Qc7 19. Qxc7+ Kxc7 20. Nxg8 Bc5 21. Nh6 f5 22. g8=Q Rd4 23. Nf7 Kb8 24. Qd8 b4 25. Bb5 Rd5 26. Ne5 Be7 27. Qxe7 Rxb5 28. Qd6+ Ka7 29. Qc7 d6 30. Nc6+ Ka6 31. Qxc8 Rc5 32. Nxb4+ Kb6 33. Qd8+ Rc7 34. Qxd6+ Rc6 35. Nxc6 e5 36. Nd8+ Ka5 37. Nxb7+ Ka4 38. Qc6+ Kb4 39. a3#) 18... bxa4 19. Nxg8 { [%cal Gg8e7,Gg7g8] } *


